01:13:00,240 --> 01:13:02,800
Or not. We don't have to use Phil's Song.
We can find another song, or...

990
01:13:02,920 --> 01:13:05,309
Hey, go ahead. Knock yourselves out.

991
01:13:09,720 --> 01:13:12,280
I mean, it's a beautiful song, Charlotte.

992
01:13:12,960 --> 01:13:15,190
It would make your dad proud.
It would be like he's there.

993
01:13:15,320 --> 01:13:17,390
Stop! Please, just stop!

994
01:13:18,240 --> 01:13:19,992
There is no us, Will. I'm not in the band.

995
01:13:20,120 --> 01:13:23,112
What? No, no, no.
Okay, we'll find another song...

996
01:13:23,400 --> 01:13:26,119
It's not about the song. I quit. I just quit.

997
01:13:26,240 --> 01:13:27,514
-Why?
-I don't do "why"!

998
01:13:27,640 --> 01:13:30,279
No, you have to. You just have to!

999
01:13:37,320 --> 01:13:38,435
Please.

1000
01:13:45,400 --> 01:13:47,391
You really want to know why?

1001
01:13:47,800 --> 01:13:50,268
Last summer, when my dad got sick,

1002
01:13:52,320 --> 01:13:55,153
I promised God, the universe,

1003
01:13:57,480 --> 01:13:59,118
anyone who'd listen,

1004
01:14:00,000 --> 01:14:01,752
that I'd be different.

1005
01:14:02,200 --> 01:14:03,599
Better. Nicer.

1006
01:14:06,640 --> 01:14:09,598
My dad hated the way I acted
when I was with Ben.

1007
01:14:10,240 --> 01:14:12,913
The way I treated kids who weren't popular.

1008
01:14:13,480 --> 01:14:14,959
So, I changed.

1009
01:14:16,120 --> 01:14:20,477
I started volunteering with the monsters.
I left my friends. I left my band.

1010
01:14:21,280 --> 01:14:24,397
I left everything that set me apart
from people like...

1011
01:14:25,800 --> 01:14:26,789
Me.

1012
01:14:30,600 --> 01:14:32,909
People like me.

1013
01:14:35,080 --> 01:14:36,832
So we were just this

1014
01:14:37,920 --> 01:14:40,639
experiment to try and make your dad okay?

1015
01:14:40,760 --> 01:14:42,512
No, I know how crazy this must sound...

1016
01:14:42,640 --> 01:14:45,473
Honestly, Charlotte,
the thing that never made sense

1017
01:14:45,600 --> 01:14:48,398
was you being my friend in the first place.

1018
01:14:51,520 --> 01:14:54,671
Hey!
While you're up there on your high horse,

1019
01:14:54,800 --> 01:14:57,837
ask yourself who are you
to judge me about lying?

1020
01:14:58,160 --> 01:14:59,229
Dewey!

1021
01:15:05,960 --> 01:15:08,155
That stands for DWl, right?

1022
01:15:08,280 --> 01:15:10,191
Driving while intoxicated?

1023
01:15:12,360 --> 01:15:14,237
I don't know what's worse.

1024
01:15:16,520 --> 01:15:21,071
Losing a father you love so much
you change your whole life for him,

1025
01:15:24,880 --> 01:15:29,158
or having a father you're so ashamed of,
you make up a whole life for him.

1026
01:16:03,960 --> 01:16:05,951
Can I have some beef jerky?

1027
01:16:06,680 --> 01:16:08,079
Is he kidding?

1028
01:16:11,440 --> 01:16:13,271
You warned me about her.

1029
01:16:14,520 --> 01:16:16,112
I didn't listen.

1030
01:16:16,240 --> 01:16:19,789
She can't help it.
It's how girls like that are hardwired.

1031
01:16:22,320 --> 01:16:24,390
How are we hardwired?

1032
01:16:25,520 --> 01:16:30,275
I mean, sure, right now, I am just a kid.

1033
01:16:30,400 --> 01:16:31,549
Whatever.

1034
01:16:34,360 --> 01:16:36,157
What's going to change?

1035
01:16:37,240 --> 01:16:38,434
Nothing.

1036
01:16:39,440 --> 01:16:41,078
I'm just going to be

1037
01:16:42,040 --> 01:16:43,234
unhappy,

1038
01:16:46,000 --> 01:16:47,115
alone,

1039
01:16:47,800 --> 01:16:51,998
scared of, like, everything.

1040
01:16:54,600 --> 01:16:56,397
You're not alone, Will.

1041
01:17:04,920 --> 01:17:07,957
Experiment? We were just her experiment?

1042
01:17:08,760 --> 01:17:10,318
I keep thinking...

1043
01:17:10,640 --> 01:17:11,629
What?

1044
01:17:11,960 --> 01:17:15,999
Well, if you were just part of
Charlotte's experiment this whole time,

1045
01:17:16,120 --> 01:17:17,872
then, what is reality?

1046
01:17:18,560 --> 01:17:20,437
What if Charlotte and her experiment are

1047
01:17:20,560 --> 01:17:23,597
really a part of someone else's
larger experiment?

1048
01:17:23,960 --> 01:17:28,476
I mean, what if we're being manipulated
by some greater intelligence than our own?

1049
01:17:28,600 --> 01:17:31,797
And if so, is there really such a thing
as free will?

1050
01:17:34,040 --> 01:17:35,268
Am I moving my hand,

1051
01:17:35,400 --> 01:17:38,836
or was it predetermined by a force
I'm not even aware of?

1052
01:17:39,480 --> 01:17:42,153
Charlotte times a trillion.

1053
01:17:50,800 --> 01:17:53,189
See, this is why you don't have friends!

1054
01:17:53,320 --> 01:17:56,517
All right, this is ridiculous! She doesn't
get to make our whole lives a lie!

1055
01:17:56,640 --> 01:17:59,712
I mean, it was real for me.
Wasn't it real for you?

1056
01:18:01,560 --> 01:18:03,835
I say we refuse to let Charlotte
screw this up for us.

1057
01:18:03,960 --> 01:18:06,030
I mean, we've worked too hard.

1058
01:18:07,960 --> 01:18:09,632
We're doing Bandslam.

1059
01:18:10,160 --> 01:18:11,195
- You're crazy.
- Why?

1060
01:18:11,320 --> 01:18:13,038
How long have you got?

1061
01:18:13,760 --> 01:18:16,433
It won't work.
What song are we going to do?

1062
01:18:16,560 --> 01:18:17,959
Phil's Song. She said we could.

1063
01:18:18,080 --> 01:18:20,548
Oh, yeah? And who's going to sing it?

1064
01:19:05,440 --> 01:19:08,113
You say your patience is longer
than my face

1065
01:19:11,040 --> 01:19:14,032
Oh, yeah, but I can see right through
your plastic case

1066
01:19:16,360 --> 01:19:19,591
Oh, you're running round
like your life is some type of race

1067
01:19:22,120 --> 01:19:25,157
You know I'm trying
but I cannot keep your pace

1068
01:19:26,720 --> 01:19:29,792
Oh, so take your blizzard
somewhere else, little girl

1069
01:19:29,920 --> 01:19:32,388
Your stormy weather ain't welcome here

1070
01:19:33,200 --> 01:19:35,111
I Can't Go On, I'll Go On.

1071
01:19:35,800 --> 01:19:37,472
Can't not buy it, buy it.

1072
01:19:42,080 --> 01:19:43,354
-Hey.
-Hey.

1073
