How are the guys holding up?
Have you been backstage?

1074
01:19:48,320 --> 01:19:51,118
Yeah, they're fine. Actually, they're great.

1075
01:19:51,400 --> 01:19:53,675
Think I'll go and wish them luck.

1076
01:19:54,640 --> 01:19:55,675
Okay.

1077
01:20:03,520 --> 01:20:05,272
Hey! Dennis Ardmore.

1078
01:20:06,600 --> 01:20:07,476
What?

1079
01:20:07,600 --> 01:20:10,273
Dennis Ardmore.
Does that name ring a bell?

1080
01:20:10,880 --> 01:20:12,279
No. Should it?

1081
01:20:12,720 --> 01:20:16,952
I guess not. I just didn't know how much
research you all had done, so...

1082
01:20:17,080 --> 01:20:19,389
But he would've been about your age now.

1083
01:20:19,520 --> 01:20:22,478
Except that Will's father got drunk in
the middle of the afternoon,

1084
01:20:22,600 --> 01:20:24,113
Iike he did every afternoon,

1085
01:20:24,240 --> 01:20:27,516
and ran him over while he was walking
home from school.

1086
01:20:29,160 --> 01:20:30,070
I heard. I'm sorry.

1087
01:20:30,200 --> 01:20:34,113
Yeah. Did you hear that Will insisted
that I bring him to the funeral?

1088
01:20:34,240 --> 01:20:36,117
That's what kind of kid he is.

1089
01:20:36,240 --> 01:20:39,994
Twelve years old, he walks right up to
Dennis Ardmore's parents,

1090
01:20:40,440 --> 01:20:42,476
and asked their forgiveness.

1091
01:20:49,440 --> 01:20:51,317
Everyone hated Will's dad.

1092
01:20:51,440 --> 01:20:53,635
Well, who wouldn't? I mean...

1093
01:20:53,760 --> 01:20:58,197
And then they put him away, and it's
like they just turned it all on his kid.

1094
01:20:58,320 --> 01:20:59,719
It was awful.

1095
01:21:01,080 --> 01:21:02,308
So just give him a break.

1096
01:21:02,440 --> 01:21:04,670
Please? Not a lot of people have.

1097
01:21:05,840 --> 01:21:10,595
So I don't know what you were planning
on saying to him, or doing, but just don't.

1098
01:21:11,360 --> 01:21:12,713
Just don't. Okay?

1099
01:21:12,840 --> 01:21:15,752
Don't make up with him. Don't be his friend.

1100
01:21:17,320 --> 01:21:18,275
Why not?

1101
01:21:18,400 --> 01:21:21,915
Because, I don't think he'll recover
if you leave him twice.

1102
01:21:25,400 --> 01:21:27,550
I've never met a kid like Will.

1103
01:21:27,960 --> 01:21:29,837
My friends have never met a kid like Will.

1104
01:21:29,960 --> 01:21:32,793
The monsters have never met a kid like Will.

1105
01:21:33,120 --> 01:21:36,795
And I want you to let me apologize to him
because I want to keep knowing him.

1106
01:21:36,920 --> 01:21:39,434
You know, I like who I am
when I'm with Will.

1107
01:21:39,560 --> 01:21:43,439
And I will do anything in the world
to be that person again.

1108
01:21:46,480 --> 01:21:47,833
So, please,

1109
01:21:50,800 --> 01:21:52,438
don't ask me not to.

1110
01:21:59,080 --> 01:22:00,115
Okay.

1111
01:22:01,200 --> 01:22:02,474
Thank you.

1112
01:22:04,120 --> 01:22:05,599
I said, "Okay." I'm not going to hug you.

1113
01:22:05,720 --> 01:22:06,630
Okay.

1114
01:22:07,480 --> 01:22:09,710
And by the way,
I'm really glad you don't wear

1115
01:22:09,840 --> 01:22:12,070
those little groupie outfits
all the time, Karen.

1116
01:22:12,200 --> 01:22:13,872
You'll need this.

1117
01:22:17,920 --> 01:22:19,148
All right.

1118
01:22:19,880 --> 01:22:22,235
And I'm so sorry about your father.

1119
01:22:41,040 --> 01:22:46,797
Tax and total it for me

1120
01:22:47,920 --> 01:22:54,075
I'll pay my bill and run so fast

1121
01:22:56,600 --> 01:23:00,559
Separation is our love now

1122
01:23:01,680 --> 01:23:03,432
Well, we're toast.

1123
01:23:04,240 --> 01:23:06,595
I don't know. They're okay.

1124
01:23:07,480 --> 01:23:08,595
I hear the band to watch

1125
01:23:08,720 --> 01:23:12,679
is I Can't Drive Stick, I'll Drive Stick,
or something like that.

1126
01:23:17,840 --> 01:23:19,717
Look, let me just speak.

1127
01:23:21,040 --> 01:23:24,635
The whole experiment thing,
not my finest hour.

1128
01:23:26,120 --> 01:23:30,432
I was angry and stupid
and really, really confused.

1129
01:23:32,240 --> 01:23:33,639
And I'm sorry.

1130
01:23:37,880 --> 01:23:39,472
Are you kidding me?

1131
01:23:39,600 --> 01:23:41,113
Okay, quick recap:

1132
01:23:41,240 --> 01:23:43,959
Charlotte dumps Ben,
turns you guys into a band,

1133
01:23:44,080 --> 01:23:46,196
finds the genius that is Will,

1134
01:23:46,320 --> 01:23:48,515
then, does one stupid thing

1135
01:23:49,720 --> 01:23:51,631
because her father has died,

1136
01:23:51,760 --> 01:23:54,035
realizes, and comes to apologize.

1137
01:23:55,920 --> 01:23:58,639
And you're not going to
accept the apology?

1138
01:24:00,400 --> 01:24:03,153
Plus, I really miss you guys.

1139
01:24:06,000 --> 01:24:07,353
Is that real?

1140
01:24:08,480 --> 01:24:09,469
Hundred percent.

1141
01:24:10,840 --> 01:24:15,356
The only thing that matters is seeing
you guys kick some serious butt tonight.

1142
01:24:16,880 --> 01:24:19,030
And you're singing Phil's Song.

1143
01:24:19,840 --> 01:24:22,035
-ls that okay?
-Yeah. Of course.

1144
01:24:23,840 --> 01:24:27,674
And I'll be the girl in front,
screaming my head off while you do.

1145
01:24:40,680 --> 01:24:42,750
Keep it hot like steam, that's your dream

1146
01:24:42,880 --> 01:24:44,359
Baby, get up off me

1147
01:24:44,720 --> 01:24:47,951
It's so clean, the way I've been
Gots me looking glossy

1148
01:24:48,080 --> 01:24:51,197
On the scene with the queen
That be acting bossy

1149
01:24:51,320 --> 01:24:54,915
I don 't want no drama, little mama
So please get up off me

1150
01:24:55,400 --> 01:24:58,517
Yeah, you know how I blow
Till you're feeling dizzy

1151
01:24:58,640 --> 01:25:00,437
Lots of soul, that's the goal

1152
01:25:02,560 --> 01:25:04,835
Yeah, go ahead. Copy that.

1153
01:25:04,960 --> 01:25:06,598
Way to be im partial.

1154
01:25:06,920 --> 01:25:09,434
Way to be realistic about your chances.

1155
01:25:10,000 --> 01:25:12,070
Way to say "way" just because I did.

1156
01:25:12,200 --> 01:25:14,760
Yeah. Standing by. Follow spots.

1157
01:25:15,480 --> 01:25:19,951
And now, from Martin Van Buren
High School in Lodi, New Jersey,

1158
01:25:20,080 --> 01:25:22,640
Ben Wheatly and the Glory Dogs!

1159
01:25:26,400 --> 01:25:27,958
You're number one!

1160
01:25:32,840 --> 01:25:34,068
Thank you.

1161
01:25:37,920 --> 01:25:39,512
Thank you so much.

1162
01:25:41,200 --> 01:25:46,228
I'd like to dedicate this next song
to someone very special to me.

1163
01:25:47,320 --> 01:25:49,038
She taught me a lot,

1164
01:25:49,160 --> 01:25:51,037
and she wrote this song.

1165
01:25:51,760 --> 01:25:54,274
So, Charlotte, this one's for you.

1166
01:25:59,120 --> 01:26:00,519
I'll never be

1167
01:26:01,400 --> 01:26:04,472
A knight in armor with a sword in hand

1168
01:26:05,400 --> 01:26:07,038
Whoa, whoa! No, no, no!

1169
01:26:08,520 --> 01:26:10,511
Don't count on me

1170
01:26:10,640 --> 01:26:14,110
To storm the barricades and take a stand

1171
01:26:14,240 --> 01:26:16,435
I didn't know. I swear. I didn't know.

1172
01:26:16,560 --> 01:26:17,879
-No, no, no.
-What?

1173
01:26:18,000 --> 01:26:19,513
You'll never see

1174
01:26:20,160 --> 01:26:23,789
It's old. Ben knew it. He probably thought
he was doing something nice for me.

1175
01:26:23,920 --> 01:26:25,990
I had no idea, Karen.
You've got to believe me!

1176
01:26:26,680 --> 01:26:28,079
I am no prince

1177
01:26:28,520 --> 01:26:29,873
I am no saint

1178
01:26:30,200 --> 01:26:33,112
I am not anyone's wildest dream

1179
01:26:33,240 --> 01:26:35,674
What are we going to do?
We can't sing the same song.

1180
01:26:35,800 --> 01:26:37,756
I don't know anything else.

1181
01:26:38,720 --> 01:26:39,709
Yes, you do.

1182
01:26:39,840 --> 01:26:42,752
And it's famous and only has, like,
four chords.

1183
01:26:43,080 --> 01:26:44,399
Alley. Now!

1184
01:26:44,520 --> 01:26:47,751
Someone to fall back on

1185
01:27:06,280 --> 01:27:10,432
Someone to fall back on

1186
01:27:28,000 --> 01:27:29,228
Come on!

1187
01:27:29,360 --> 01:27:30,395
We need another minute.

1188
01:27:30,520 --> 01:27:31,589
We don't have another minute! They just...

1189
01:27:31,720 --> 01:27:33,790
We need another minute!

1190
01:27:39,840 --> 01:27:43,196
Our last band is also from
Martin Van Buren High.

1191
01:27:43,560 --> 01:27:45,790
I don't know what they're putting
in the water in Lodi,

1192
01:27:45,920 --> 01:27:49,435
